content.text:
One script, heredocs for file content:

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash

mkdir -p src include

cat > src/main.c << 'EOF'
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    return 0;
}
EOF

cat > CMakeLists.txt << 'EOF'
cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.10)
project(my_project)
EOF
```

`'EOF'` (quoted) prevents `$variable` expansion inside the content. That's the standard approach — one file, no deps.

