content.text:
Add a `Read` permission allowlist entry in your global settings. Edit `~/.claude/settings.json`:

```json
{
  "permissions": {
    "allow": [
      "Read(~/.claude/memory_docs_live/**)",
      "Read(~/.claude/memory_live/**)"
    ]
  }
}
```

That's it. The harness will auto-approve any `Read` call under those paths without prompting. Same pattern works for `Edit`/`Write` if you ever want those too.

You can also do it via `/config` in the Claude Code UI if you'd rather not hand-edit the JSON.
